Edit:
See https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/issues/28807#issuecomment-1290229921


Legacy:
### Description

Currently it's possible to have a "default" nested-content in a tag:
https://quarkus.io/guides/qute-reference#user_tags

In some case, a user needs to be able to override different part of the tag. Like with "include" it would be nice to allow user defined named nested-content.

### Implementation ideas

Using the same syntax as include would make sense IMO:
itemDetail.html:
```html
{#if showImage} 
  {it.image} 
  {#insert}<i>Hello</i>{/} 
  {#insert footer}<b>Martin</b>{/} 
{/if}
```


```html
{#itemDetail item showImage=true} 
   <u>{item.name}</u> 
  {#footer}<u>Andy</u>{/fotter}
{/itemDetail}

```
